The President and First Lady welcomed several thousand people to the White House for a celebration. They thanked everyone for their support, especially military families. The First Lady also expressed gratitude to the military band. The President mentioned a shooting in Chicago and expressed condolences for the victims. He emphasized the need to control gun violence. The President and First Lady wished everyone a happy Fourth of July and urged them to head home safely. They concluded by saying, "God bless America" and "God protect our troops."